The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Dec. 19: The government will bring out a white paper on divestment in central public sector enterprises after completing the review process. The white paper will be placed for information of Parliament after the review by the government is completed, finance minister P. Chidambaram informed the Lok Sabha in his action-taken report on the implementation of recommendations of the standing committee of finance.

 Mumbai, Dec. 19: UBS Securities Asia has picked up a 0.53 per cent stake in PTC India for Rs 4.12 crore in open market transactions. UBS acquired 8.01 lakh shares at a price of Rs 51.53 each.

 New Delhi, Dec. 19: Tata Power Company expects to arrange funds by August 2007 for the 4,000-mw Mundra ultra power project to be set up at an estimated cost of Rs 20,000 crore.

 Mumbai, Dec. 19: The Reserve Bank today proposed that banks should make financial disclosures on their exposure to individuals, companies and statutory bodies from September 30, 2007. In its draft guidelines, the RBI has proposed inclusion of retail banking and corporate/wholesale banking to the list of segment reporting. 

 New Delhi, Dec. 19: Officers of central public sector units will go an indefinite nation-wide strike from December 22, demanding higher salaries and autonomy for the public sector.




